391 stateString = tuple[ 3 ];

394 promise[ tuple[1] ] = list.add;

511 chainable = true;

786 );
787
788 // Check for headers option
789 for ( i in s.headers ) {
790 jqXHR.setRequestHeader( i, s.headers[ i ] );
791 }
792
793 // Allow custom headers/mimetypes and early abort
794 if ( s.beforeSend && ( s.beforeSend.call( callbackContext, jqXHR, s ) === false || state === 2 ) ) {
795 // Abort if not done already and return
796 return jqXHR.abort();
797 }
798
799 // aborting is no longer a cancellation
800 strAbort = "abort";
801
802 // Install callbacks on deferreds
803 for ( i in { success: 1, error: 1, complete: 1 } ) {
804 jqXHR[ i ]( s[ i ] );
805 }
806
807 // Get transport
808 transport = inspectPrefiltersOrTransports( transports, s, options, jqXHR );
809
810 // If no transport, we auto-abort
811 if ( !transport ) {
812 done( -1, "No Transport" );
813 } else {
814 jqXHR.readyState = 1;
815
816 // Send global event
817 if ( fireGlobals ) {
818 globalEventContext.trigger( "ajaxSend", [ jqXHR, s ] );
819 }
820 // Timeout
821 if ( s.async && s.timeout > 0 ) {
822 timeoutTimer = setTimeout(function() {
823 jqXHR.abort("timeout");
824 }, s.timeout );
825 }
826
827 try {
828 state = 1;
829 transport.send( requestHeaders, done );
830 } catch ( e ) {
831 // Propagate exception as error if not done
832 if ( state < 2 ) {
833 done( -1, e );
834 // Simply rethrow otherwise
835 } else {
836 throw e;
837 }
838 }
839 }
840
841 // Callback for when everything is done
842 function done( status, nativeStatusText, responses, headers ) {
843 var isSuccess, success, error, response, modified,
844 statusText = nativeStatusText;
845
846 // Called once
847 if ( state === 2 ) {
848 return;
849 }
850
851 // State is "done" now
852 state = 2;
853
854 // Clear timeout if it exists
855 if ( timeoutTimer ) {
856 clearTimeout( timeoutTimer );
857 }
858
859 // Dereference transport for early garbage collection
860 // (no matter how long the jqXHR object will be used)
861 transport = undefined;
862
863 // Cache response headers
864 responseHeadersString = headers || "";
865
866 // Set readyState
867 jqXHR.readyState = status > 0 ? 4 : 0;
868
869 // Determine if successful
870 isSuccess = status >= 200 && status < 300 || status === 304;
871
872 // Get response data
873 if ( responses ) {
874 response = ajaxHandleResponses( s, jqXHR, responses );
875 }
876
877 // Convert no matter what (that way responseXXX fields are always set)
878 response = ajaxConvert( s, response, jqXHR, isSuccess );
879
880 // If successful, handle type chaining
881 if ( isSuccess ) {
882
883 // Set the If-Modified-Since and/or If-None-Match header, if in ifModified mode.
884 if ( s.ifModified ) {
885 modified = jqXHR.getResponseHeader("Last-Modified");
886 if ( modified ) {
887 jQuery.lastModified[ cacheURL ] = modified;
888 }
889 modified = jqXHR.getResponseHeader("etag");
890 if ( modified ) {
891 jQuery.etag[ cacheURL ] = modified;
892 }
893 }
894
895 // if no content
896 if ( status === 204 || s.type === "HEAD" ) {
897 statusText = "nocontent";
898
899 // if not modified
900 } else if ( status === 304 ) {
901 statusText = "notmodified";
902
903 // If we have data, let's convert it
904 } else {
905 statusText = response.state;
906 success = response.data;
907 error = response.error;
908 isSuccess = !error;
909 }
910 } else {
911 // We extract error from statusText
912 // then normalize statusText and status for non-aborts
913 error = statusText;
914 if ( status || !statusText ) {
915 statusText = "error";
916 if ( status < 0 ) {
917 status = 0;
918 }
919 }
920 }
921
922 // Set data for the fake xhr object
923 jqXHR.status = status;
924 jqXHR.statusText = ( nativeStatusText || statusText ) + "";
925
926 // Success/Error
927 if ( isSuccess ) {
928 deferred.resolveWith( callbackContext, [ success, statusText, jqXHR ] );
929 } else {
930 deferred.rejectWith( callbackContext, [ jqXHR, statusText, error ] );
931 }
932
933 // Status-dependent callbacks
934 jqXHR.statusCode( statusCode );
935 statusCode = undefined;
936
937 if ( fireGlobals ) {
938 globalEventContext.trigger( isSuccess ? "ajaxSuccess" : "ajaxError",
939 [ jqXHR, s, isSuccess ? success : error ] );
940 }
941
942 // Complete
943 completeDeferred.fireWith( callbackContext, [ jqXHR, statusText ] );
944
945 if ( fireGlobals ) {
946 globalEventContext.trigger( "ajaxComplete", [ jqXHR, s ] );
947 // Handle the global AJAX counter
948 if ( !( --jQuery.active ) ) {
949 jQuery.event.trigger("ajaxStop");
950 }
951 }
952 }
953
954 return jqXHR;
955 };

1577 jQuery.extend = function() {
1578 /// <summary>
1579 /// Merge the contents of two or more objects together into the first object.
1580 /// &#10;1 - jQuery.extend(target, object1, objectN)
1581 /// &#10;2 - jQuery.extend(deep, target, object1, objectN)
1582 /// </summary>
1583 /// <param name="" type="Boolean">
1584 /// If true, the merge becomes recursive (aka. deep copy).
1585 /// </param>
1586 /// <param name="" type="Object">
1587 /// The object to extend. It will receive the new properties.
1588 /// </param>
1589 /// <param name="" type="Object">
1590 /// An object containing additional properties to merge in.
1591 /// </param>
1592 /// <param name="" type="Object">
1593 /// Additional objects containing properties to merge in.
1594 /// </param>
1595 /// <returns type="Object" />
1596
1597 var src, copyIsArray, copy, name, options, clone,
1598 target = arguments[0] || {},
1599 i = 1,
1600 length = arguments.length,
1601 deep = false;
1602
1603 // Handle a deep copy situation
1604 if ( typeof target === "boolean" ) {
1605 deep = target;
1606 target = arguments[1] || {};
1607 // skip the boolean and the target
1608 i = 2;
1609 }
1610
1611 // Handle case when target is a string or something (possible in deep copy)
1612 if ( typeof target !== "object" && !jQuery.isFunction(target) ) {
1613 target = {};
1614 }
1615
1616 // extend jQuery itself if only one argument is passed
1617 if ( length === i ) {
1618 target = this;
1619 --i;
1620 }
1621
1622 for ( ; i < length; i++ ) {
1623 // Only deal with non-null/undefined values
1624 if ( (options = arguments[ i ]) != null ) {
1625 // Extend the base object
1626 for ( name in options ) {
1627 src = target[ name ];
1628 copy = options[ name ];
1629
1630 // Prevent never-ending loop
1631 if ( target === copy ) {
1632 continue;
1633 }
1634
1635 // Recurse if we're merging plain objects or arrays
1636 if ( deep && copy && ( jQuery.isPlainObject(copy) || (copyIsArray = jQuery.isArray(copy)) ) ) {
1637 if ( copyIsArray ) {
1638 copyIsArray = false;
1639 clone = src && jQuery.isArray(src) ? src : [];
1640
1641 } else {
1642 clone = src && jQuery.isPlainObject(src) ? src : {};
1643 }
1644
1645 // Never move original objects, clone them
1646 target[ name ] = jQuery.extend( deep, clone, copy );
1647
1648 // Don't bring in undefined values
1649 } else if ( copy !== undefined ) {
1650 target[ name ] = copy;
1651 }
1652 }
1653 }
1654 }
1655
1656 // Return the modified object
1657 return target;
1658 };

3858 jQuery.prototype.extend = function() {
3859
3860 var src, copyIsArray, copy, name, options, clone,
3861 target = arguments[0] || {},
3862 i = 1,
3863 length = arguments.length,
3864 deep = false;
3865
3866 // Handle a deep copy situation
3867 if ( typeof target === "boolean" ) {
3868 deep = target;
3869 target = arguments[1] || {};
3870 // skip the boolean and the target
3871 i = 2;
3872 }
3873
3874 // Handle case when target is a string or something (possible in deep copy)
3875 if ( typeof target !== "object" && !jQuery.isFunction(target) ) {
3876 target = {};
3877 }
3878

3880 if ( length === i ) {
3881 target = this;
3882 --i;
3883 }
3884
3885 for ( ; i < length; i++ ) {
3886 // Only deal with non-null/undefined values
3887 if ( (options = arguments[ i ]) != null ) {
3888 // Extend the base object
3889 for ( name in options ) {
3890 src = target[ name ];
3891 copy = options[ name ];
3892
3893 // Prevent never-ending loop
3894 if ( target === copy ) {
3895 continue;
3896 }
3897
3898 // Recurse if we're merging plain objects or arrays
3899 if ( deep && copy && ( jQuery.isPlainObject(copy) || (copyIsArray = jQuery.isArray(copy)) ) ) {
3900 if ( copyIsArray ) {
3901 copyIsArray = false;
3902 clone = src && jQuery.isArray(src) ? src : [];
3903
3904 } else {
3905 clone = src && jQuery.isPlainObject(src) ? src : {};
3906 }
3907
3908 // Never move original objects, clone them
3909 target[ name ] = jQuery.extend( deep, clone, copy );
3910
3911 // Don't bring in undefined values
3912 } else if ( copy !== undefined ) {
3913 target[ name ] = copy;
3914 }
3915 }
3916 }
3917 }
3918
3919 // Return the modified object
3920 return target;

6395 /// One or more class names (separated by spaces) to be toggled for each element in the matched set.
6396 /// </param>
6397 /// <param name="stateVal" type="Boolean">
6398 /// A Boolean (not just truthy/falsy) value to determine whether the class should be added or removed.
6399 /// </param>
6400 /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6401
6402 var type = typeof value,
6403 isBool = typeof stateVal === "boolean";
6404
6405 if ( jQuery.isFunction( value ) ) {
6406 return this.each(function( i ) {
6407 jQuery( this ).toggleClass( value.call(this, i, this.className, stateVal), stateVal );
6408 });
6409 }
6410
6411 return this.each(function() {
6412 if ( type === "string" ) {
6413 // toggle individual class names
6414 var className,
6415 i = 0,
6416 self = jQuery( this ),
6417 state = stateVal,
6418 classNames = value.match( core_rnotwhite ) || [];
6419
6420 while ( (className = classNames[ i++ ]) ) {
6421 // check each className given, space separated list
6422 state = isBool ? state : !self.hasClass( className );
6423 self[ state ? "addClass" : "removeClass" ]( className );
6424 }
6425
6426 // Toggle whole class name
6427 } else if ( type === core_strundefined || type === "boolean" ) {
6428 if ( this.className ) {
6429 // store className if set
6430 jQuery._data( this, "__className__", this.className );
6431 }
6432
6433 // If the element has a class name or if we're passed "false",
6434 // then remove the whole classname (if there was one, the above saved it).
6435 // Otherwise bring back whatever was previously saved (if anything),
6436 // falling back to the empty string if nothing was stored.
6437 this.className = this.className || value === false ? "" : jQuery._data( this, "__className__" ) || "";
6438 }
6439 });
6440 };

6546 jQuery.prototype.val = function( value ) {
6547 /// <summary>
6548 /// 1: Get the current value of the first element in the set of matched elements.
6549 /// &#10; 1.1 - val()
6550 /// &#10;2: Set the value of each element in the set of matched elements.
6551 /// &#10; 2.1 - val(value)
6552 /// &#10; 2.2 - val(function(index, value))
6553 /// </summary>
6554 /// <param name="value" type="String">
6555 /// A string of text or an array of strings corresponding to the value of each matched element to set as selected/checked.
6556 /// </param>
6557 /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6558
6559 var ret, hooks, isFunction,
6560 elem = this[0];
6561
6562 if ( !arguments.length ) {
6563 if ( elem ) {
6564 hooks = jQuery.valHooks[ elem.type ] || jQuery.valHooks[ elem.nodeName.toLowerCase() ];
6565
6566 if ( hooks && "get" in hooks && (ret = hooks.get( elem, "value" )) !== undefined ) {
6567 return ret;
6568 }
6569
6570 ret = elem.value;
6571
6572 return typeof ret === "string" ?
6573 // handle most common string cases
6574 ret.replace(rreturn, "") :
6575 // handle cases where value is null/undef or number
6576 ret == null ? "" : ret;
6577 }
6578
6579 return;
6580 }
6581
6582 isFunction = jQuery.isFunction( value );
6583
6584 return this.each(function( i ) {
6585 var val;
6586
6587 if ( this.nodeType !== 1 ) {
6588 return;
6589 }
6590
6591 if ( isFunction ) {
6592 val = value.call( this, i, jQuery( this ).val() );
6593 } else {
6594 val = value;
6595 }
6596
6597 // Treat null/undefined as ""; convert numbers to string
6598 if ( val == null ) {
6599 val = "";
6600 } else if ( typeof val === "number" ) {
6601 val += "";
6602 } else if ( jQuery.isArray( val ) ) {
6603 val = jQuery.map(val, function ( value ) {
6604 return value == null ? "" : value + "";
6605 });
6606 }
6607
6608 hooks = jQuery.valHooks[ this.type ] || jQuery.valHooks[ this.nodeName.toLowerCase() ];
6609
6610 // If set returns undefined, fall back to normal setting
6611 if ( !hooks || !("set" in hooks) || hooks.set( this, val, "value" ) === undefined ) {
6612 this.value = val;
6613 }
6614 });
6615 };

6617 /// <summary>
6618 /// 1: Get the current computed width for the first element in the set of matched elements.
6619 /// &#10; 1.1 - width()
6620 /// &#10;2: Set the CSS width of each element in the set of matched elements.
6621 /// &#10; 2.1 - width(value)
6622 /// &#10; 2.2 - width(function(index, width))
6623 /// </summary>
6624 /// <param name="margin" type="Number">
6625 /// An integer representing the number of pixels, or an integer along with an optional unit of measure appended (as a string).
6626 /// </param>
6627 /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6628
6629 var chainable = arguments.length && ( defaultExtra || typeof margin !== "boolean" ),
6630 extra = defaultExtra || ( margin === true || value === true ? "margin" : "border" );

6633 var doc;
6634
6635 if ( jQuery.isWindow( elem ) ) {
